      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive model justified for titanium alloy under sub-yield loading; contact formulation validated.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw and UHMWPE surrogate bone blocks modeled as linear elastic isotropic materials, appropriate for the pre-yield regime targeted by F1717. Augmented Lagrangian contact at screw-block interface captures load transfer without artificial penetration. Model form uncertainty bounded by comparison to nonlinear elasto-plastic sensitivity runs showing <3% QoI difference below yield. Required level 3 achieved."
