      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to pedicle screw mechanical performance assessment for 510(k) submission. These QoIs map to the clinical failure modes of construct loosening (stiffness) and screw fracture (yield force). Relevance fully justified. Required level 3 achieved."
